title: [To research/auto-aligned]Add autoaligned time series
body:
## Description
We add "autoaligned" keyword for iotdb. A grouping algorithm is devised for autoaligned time series.


### create syntax
use `create autoaligned  timeseries root.sg1.d1.s1(c1 INT32, c2 DOUBLE, c3 FLOAT)` for creating the timeseries

### insert syntax
use `insert into  root.sg1.d1.s1(time, s1, s2, s3) autoaligned values(1, 1, 1, 1)` for inserting data

### column-grouping algorithm 
The column-grouping algorithm has been devised. When the data are flushed into disk, the algorithm will give a strategy for grouping the time series.

We add encoding algorithms: RLBE, RAKE and SPRINTZ to IoTDB. This work is supported by SRT 2022.

Encoding classes are added and updated. We create new classes: RLBE, SprintzEncoder and RAKEEncoder extends the class Encoder. Subclasses of handling different datatype extend the three new encoding classes.
### Decoding
Decoding classes are added and updated. We create new classes to decode RLBE, RAKE and Sprintz code words, and subclasses of handling different datatype extend the decode classes are also created.
### Related
TSEncoding class is updated to support new encoding algorithms, SQL lexical analyse parts are also updated to support new encoding algorithms.

title: [IOTDB-2510] Reconstructing the password encryption mode
body:
1. We can adapt to different password encryption modes based on our requirements. 
2. MD5 is not a secure encryption mode and can be decrypted.
Reasons for abstracting the three interfaces:
1. Extract the parameter parameter. The salt parameter is required for encryption. Different parameters affect the encryption performance.
2. The interface extracts the validate method because some encryption algorithms do not simply compare whether the encrypted character strings are the same. The ciphertext needs to be split and compared by segment.
3. Extract the encryption method, which is a common method. Each encryption algorithm can be adapted freely.

1. 提取parameter配置，有一些非对称加密需要盐值参数，不同的参数影响加密性能。

In IoTDB, `splitPathToDetachedPath()` in `MetaUtils` is often called to convert `String` to `PartialPath`. However, some time series cannot be used normally due to ambiguity, even if they are created.

[root, sg, "s1"."s2"] vs [root, sg, "s1", "s2"]
[root, sg, "a."] vs [root, sg, "a, "]
[root, sg, "ab, cd"] vs [root, sg, "ab.cd"]
```

After this PR,
- Quotes can only be escaped with a backslash(`\`)
- Backslashe will be stored as part of the node name

```
[root, sg, "s1\".\"s2"] vs [root, sg, "s1", "s2"]
[root, sg, "a."] vs [root, sg, \"a, \"]

title: [IOTDB-2509] [IOTDB-2445]select count(*) execution failed : overlapped data should be consumed first
body:
(1) Problem: Currently, cross space compaction may cause unseq data in target files.
(2) Reason: When selecting the source files, it will skip files which are being compacted. For example, seq files 1 2 3 have overlap with unseq file 4, but the file 1 2 are being compacted, so they will only choose file 3 and 4 as the source files in this cross space compaction, this will lead a overlap between the target file and seq files 1 2.
(3) Solution: When selecting files, we need to select all seq files that overlap with unseq files (no matter whether they are being compacted or not). After selecting files, we need to determine whether there are source files being compacted before throwing the task into the queue. If there are, this compaction task is discarded.

As a conclusion, this pr fix cross space compaction selector bug to avoid unseq data in target files.

### Problem
During concurrent timeseries auto creation, MTree will throw NPE.
See  IOTDB-2476

### Cause
The replacement operation of EntityMNode is not a synchronized operation, thus a thread will read a null between the deletion and addition, which is the existing implementation of repalcement.

### Solution
Use replace method of ConcurrentHashMap to make the node replacement a synchronized operation and make the replace method of MNode a synchronized operation.
